<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Feign" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Feign,</orth> 1) to invent, to image; a) trans.: <cit><quote>the poet did f. that Orpheus drew trees,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 5.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 80</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>all that poets f. of bliss and joy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I have upon a high and pleasant hill --ed Fortune to be throned,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thou hast --ed him a worthy fellow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 64</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 64</bibl> b) absol.: <cit><quote>as poets f.</quote> <bibl n="shak. pp 115" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 115</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the truest poetry is the most --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 3, 20</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to pretend, to counterfeit, to dissemble; a) trans.: <cit><quote>your --ed tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 425" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 425</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>it is the more like to be --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.208" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 208</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.190" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 1, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 4, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 2, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.279" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 279</bibl>. b) intr. <cit><quote>with --ing voice verses of --ing love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 31</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most friendship is --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.181" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 181</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 22</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.140.110" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 140</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.152" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.5.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 5, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 67</bibl> (Qq <emph>fawning</emph>).
